In the first and nineteenth lines the word emente has been substituted for arcere, which word seems originally in each case to have ended the line, In the fifteenth line the word somnum has been altered to somnos. In the twenty-fourth line portions of the paper (which is very much decayed) are torn away, and the verse is necessarily now imperfect.
